# Project Rules

## Directory Structure (Update This Section On File Changes)

```text
.
|-- .cursor/
|   `-- rules/
|       `-- python-project-standards.mdc
|-- .gitignore
|-- README.md
|-- dashboard.html
|-- demo_responses.csv
|-- demo_word_count.py
`-- HCDE 530/
    `-- HCDE 530 week 2/
        |-- .gitignore
        |-- README.md
        |-- dashboard.html
        |-- demo_responses.csv
        `-- demo_word_count.py
```

## Maintenance Requirement

- When any file or folder is added, removed, moved, or renamed, update the
  "Directory Structure" section in this file in the same change.
- Keep the structure concise and only include source/project files (skip `.git`
  internals and OS files like `.DS_Store`).
- Keep paths and names exactly as they appear in the repository.

## Coding Preferences

- Prefer simple, readable Python and HTML for coursework.
- Avoid adding dependencies unless explicitly requested.
- Keep data file names stable unless the user asks for a rename.
